    "Algorithm 1 Abstract System ArchitectureInitialize model M with parameters θ Define Google Query API function GQ(q) for each inputx do Generate context-based query q ← f (x) if q is not null then y ← GQ(q) ▷ Query Google API Process API response r ← g(y) Update model context C ← h(C, r) end if Generate output o ← M(x, C; θ) Return o end forThis algorithm outlines the core steps involved in the system's operation.",
    "The process begins with the initialization of the model and the definition of the function to interact with the Google Query API.",
    "For each input, a context-based query is formulated and, if applicable, sent to the API.",
    "The response is processed and used to update the model's context before generating the output.",
    "This iterative process ensures that the model leverages real-time information to enhance the accuracy and relevance of its generated text."
  ],
